We used the method of Yachi et al. (2016) for the estimation. First, we obtained the annual shipping amount for each insecticide product by prefecture from Nouyaku-youran, pesticide handbooks published by the Japan Plant Protection Association, from 1989 to 2011. Second, we estimated the fraction of usage of each insecticide product for nursery-box treatment of rice seedlings from the application list for each product. Third, we multiplied the shipping amount by the fraction of usage of each product and by the percentage content of the active ingredient. We summed these usage amounts to calculate the usage amount for each active ingredient of the insecticides in each prefecture and each year. From the data of estimated usage amount for each insecticide applied to nursery boxes, we calculated the annual usage ratio of each insecticide in each prefecture as follows (Yachi et al. 2017):\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
